LOCATION: Communications Bay, Deck 7
STATUS: Training Mode Active
ACCESS: GRANTED

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The Communications Bay hums with the soft glow of status indicators. Banks of
network terminals line the walls, their screens displaying packet flows and
connection states. This is where all station communications are routed - from
simple intercom messages to critical Earth transmissions.

Chief Communications Officer Park left hastily when the solar flare hit.
Her workstation still shows the last diagnostic she was running. A coffee
cup sits cold beside a worn copy of "TCP/IP Illustrated."

    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │                                                                     │
    │  NEXUS: This is where you'll learn the fundamentals, Specialist.   │
    │                                                                     │
    │         Before we can fix the network, you must understand how     │
    │         it works. Every packet that flows through this station     │
    │         follows the same rules that govern all networks.           │
    │                                                                     │
    │         In this module, you will master:                           │
    │                                                                     │
    │         • IP addressing and container configuration                │
    │         • Connectivity testing with ping                           │
    │         • DNS resolution and name services                         │
    │                                                                     │
    │         Officer Park's notes are still here. She was thorough.     │
    │         Follow her methodology and you'll understand these         │
    │         systems as well as she did.                                │
    │                                                                     │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

MODULE MISSIONS
═══════════════

    [1] ip-discovery     Explore Container Network Configuration
    [2] connectivity     Test Network Reachability with Ping
    [3] dns-resolution   Understand Name Resolution

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

SKILLS YOU WILL LEARN
═════════════════════

    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │  COMMAND          │  PURPOSE                                       │
    ├───────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │  ip addr          │  View network interface configuration          │
    │  ip route         │  Display routing table                         │
    │  ping             │  Test connectivity to remote hosts             │
    │  dig              │  Query DNS servers                             │
    │  nslookup         │  Simple DNS lookups                            │
    │  cat /etc/resolv.conf │  View DNS configuration                    │
